text: The Legislative Assembly of the Northern Territory is the only house of the Parliament of the Northern Territory, Australia. The Legislative Assembly has 25 members that are each elected for single-member electorates. The Legislative Assembly replaced the Northern Territory Legislative Council in 1974. ==References== ==Other websites== * Northern Territory Legislative Assembly Category:1974 establishments in Australia Category:Parliament of the Northern Territory Category:Legislatures of country subdivisions
